Starting from January 5, 2025, the High-Speed Rail (Hong Kong Section) will introduce the following service enhancements and adjustments:

● Launch a new long-haul line to Xi’anbei, stopping at new stations including Luoyang Longmen and Huashanbei and provides one pair of northbound and southbound train trips daily;

● Enhance train services to Shenzhenbei Station, Shanwei Station, and Wuhan Station, with one additional pair of train trips being added daily;

● The Shanghai Hongqiao line (non-sleeper trains) will be adjusted to stop at Nanchangxi Station, Huangshanbei Station, Hangzhouxi Station, and Suzhounan Station (commencing from January 5*);

● A pair of trains originally departing/terminating at Chaoshan Station will be rerouted to Meizhouxi Station, with a new intermediate stop at Longchuanxi Station (commencing January 5). 

Tickets for the newly added trains are now on sale. Tickets are available for sale through the 12306 official website (12306. cn) or mobile app; appointed travel agents (Click here); or at Hong Kong West Kowloon Station. 

*G99, G6504: stop service on January 4, commencing new route from January 5;

G6503, G100: stop service on January 5, commencing new route from January 6.
